Business Brief -- UAL Corp.:
   United Air's Parent to Post
   Record Loss for 4th Quarter
For the first nine months of 1991, the holding company
reported a loss of $79.3 million.
   United said the estimated fourth-quarter loss "will
reflect, among other things, a significant amount of
non-recurring expenses."
   UAL's stock fell $3.25, to $155.75, in composite trading
Friday on the New York Stock Exchange.
   UAL's leading rival, AMR Corp., parent of American
Airlines, recently reported a $129.4 million fourth-quarter
loss.